                            <comment id="13063365" author="mgrigorov" created="Mon, 11 Jul 2011 14:37:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With &lt;br/&gt;
=====================&lt;br/&gt;
Revision 915613 - (view) (download) (annotate) - &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;select for diffs&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
Modified Wed Feb 24 00:21:13 2010 UTC (16 months, 2 weeks ago) by knopp &lt;br/&gt;
Original Path: wicket/trunk/wicket/src/main/java/org/apache/wicket/protocol/http/servlet/ServletWebResponse.java &lt;br/&gt;
File length: 5846 byte(s) &lt;br/&gt;
Diff to previous 912510 (colored)&lt;br/&gt;
RestartResponseOnInterceptPageException&lt;br/&gt;
Upgraded jetty&lt;br/&gt;
=====================&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;org.apache.wicket.protocol.http.servlet.ServletWebResponse.sendRedirect(String) have been changed to produce absolute url.&lt;br/&gt;
Commenting &quot;url = getAbsoluteURL(url);&quot; (line 244, in current trunk) fixes the problem. No tests fail.&lt;br/&gt;
By Servlet spec javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse.sendRedirect(String) should resolve any relative url passed to it.&lt;br/&gt;
For Ajax requests we return &quot;&amp;lt;ajax-response&amp;gt;&amp;lt;redirect&amp;gt;&amp;lt;![CDATA&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;THE URL HERE&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;]&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/redirect&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/ajax-response&amp;gt;&quot; and it works OK again.&lt;br/&gt;
I see no reason for this &quot;getAbsoluteURL(url)&quot; call.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13063402" author="ivaynberg" created="Mon, 11 Jul 2011 15:42:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes, seems weird indeed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
